{"id":14881776,"mediaExerciseId":"61b6092b-5231-4d9f-a961-30d3643b30e9","exerciseName":"8","chapterName":"21","chapterTitle":"International Corporate Finance","groupId":612471,"groupTitle":"Questions and Problems","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":737,"solutions":[{"id":5985723,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this exercise, we are asked to determine the difference in the annual inflation rates for the United States and Poland.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"A **purchasing power parity** refers to the thought that the exchange rate adjusts in order to keep a *constant purchasing power* among the currencies. There are **two forms** of PPP, the *absolute* PPP and *relative* PPP.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"A **relative purchasing power parity** refers to the concept that there is a *change in exchange rate* that can be determined by the *difference of the inflation rate* of two countries.  ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"The formula to determine the exchange rate based on the relative purchasing power parity is as follows:\n\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$E(S_{3})$} &=\\text{$S_{0}$}\\times[ 1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}]^t\\\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n\nwherein: \n\n$E(S_{t})$ = Expected exchange rate in *t* periods \n\n$S_{0}$ = Current spot exchange rate \n\n$h_{FC}$ = Foreign country inflation rate \n\n$h_{US}$ = Inflation rate in the US","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/d99cf4efb413223b9d69c4df1ef46faa/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/d99cf4efb413223b9d69c4df1ef46faa/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"We are given the following data:\n\n<center>\n\n| |Polish zloty | \n|--|--| \n|current exchange rate | Z 4.04| \n|expected exchange rate in three years|Z 4.13|","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":138,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/fcb8b7450ff037d68a8bfcc2177643b0/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/fcb8b7450ff037d68a8bfcc2177643b0/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"We will apply the formula of relative purchasing power parity to determine the difference in the inflation rates for the United States and Poland. The computation is as follows:\n$$ \\begin{aligned}\n\\text{$E(S_{3})$} &=\\text{$S_{0}$}\\times[ 1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}]^t\\\\[15pt]\n\\text{Z 4.13}&=\\text{Z 4.04}\\times[ 1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}]^3\\\\[15pt]\n\\dfrac{\\text{Z 4.13}}{\\text{Z 4.04}}&=1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}^3\\\\[15pt]\n{\\text{Z 1.0223}}^{1/3}&=1+\\text{($h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$)}\\\\[15pt]\n\\text{$h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$} &=1.0074-1\\\\[15pt]\n\\text{$h_{FC}$-$h_{US}$} &=\\boxed{\\text{0.0074 or 0.74\\%}}\n\\end{aligned}$$","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":100,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/d84b237b882e9f4658743c5501958555/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":51,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/d84b237b882e9f4658743c5501958555/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6},{"columns":[{"text":"As a conclusion, the difference in the annual inflation rates for the United States and Poland is **0.74%** determined by the relative purchasing power parity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":303,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/fc82c5b4d301580da0d3dad54b6879c5/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":153,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/22/01/05/857b1dee919bfa8b4180068e0d89869e/fc82c5b4d301580da0d3dad54b6879c5/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":7}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"d09b16f0-7640-45d7-a1bd-7074480cd86f","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":7}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14881777,"exerciseName":"9","page":737,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"c8a4bd02-da8e-41f9-9995-0aa9c2ccd01a","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-21-questions-and-problems-9-c8a4bd02-da8e-41f9-9995-0aa9c2ccd01a"},{"id":14881778,"exerciseName":"10","page":737,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"de5d2fef-df82-4d4f-92d9-28b14cb968ea","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/f